summary: Do you know what, abstractly, is kinda hilarious about killing eve?
body:
Do you know what, abstractly, is kinda hilarious about killing eve?

Eve starts calling villanelle “villanelle” after getting the perfume from her.

Like sure, it turns out to be what she goes by, but what if she just sent her some nice perfume. Was she just gonna call her that no matter what? “Ah yes I’ve found out what to call the bad guy. Lynx body spray”

summary:
The most accurate description of Killling Eve I’ve heard:
“Making for a complex psychological thriller that is both nail-biting...
body:
The most accurate description of Killling Eve I’ve heard:

“Making for a complex psychological thriller that is both nail-biting and mind-bending, this riveting story plays out like a game of chess, in which the final outcome could mean their ultimate demise. ‘Game’ is the key word in all of this, as Villanelle treats the world as her own personal playground. The question is if she views Eve as just another pawn or her queen.”
